We solve this quadratic equation using the quadratic formula \( r = \frac{-b \pm \sqrt{b^2 - 4ac}}{2a} \), where \( a = 1 \), \( b = -6 \), and \( c = -9 \):
\[
r = \frac{-(-6) \pm \sqrt{(-6)^2 - 4 \cdot 1 \cdot (-9)}}{2 \cdot 1}
\]
\[
r = \frac{6 \pm \sqrt{36 + 36}}{2}
\]
\[
r = \frac{6 \pm \sqrt{72}}{2}
\]
\[
r = \frac{6 \pm 6\sqrt{2}}{2}
\]
\[
r = 3 \pm 3\sqrt{2}
\]
